sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) as total_activities
FROM activities
WHERE resource_id = 1 AND status = 'completed';

external_knowledge:
- "busiest individuals" refers to patients with the highest number of activities;
- "top trio" means to select the top 3 patients with the most activities;
- "involvement in activities" pertains to the count of activities each patient has undertaken.

sql:
SELECT p.patient_name, c.status
FROM patients p
JOIN cases c ON p.patient_id = c.patient_id;

SELECT activity_name
FROM activities
WHERE activity_id = 1;
